description: Anthony Davis recorded a season-high 41 points, along with 9 rebounds for the Lakers in his return to New Orleans as they defeated the Pelicans, 114-110. Davis‚Äô 41 points tonight are the most points ever scored against a former team in a player‚Äôs first matchup against them, passing Danny Ainge, Stephon Marbury and Kevin Durant, who each tallied 39 points in their first game against their former team.
